    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Get Started with B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Manage Storefront Details and Metadata\n Set Up Product Data for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Help Buyers Discover Products on Your Storefront\n Price and Sell Products for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Support Buyer Accounts for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Provide a Smooth Path to Purchase for Storefront Buyers\n Customize the Storefront User Experience\n Considerations for Storefront User Experience Customizations\n Configure the Default Storefront Pages\n Home Page\n Checkout Page\n My Account Page\n Product Compare Page\n Product Detail Page\n Configure Product Info and Options on the Product Detail Page\n Guidelines for Creating Page Sections\n Show a Product's Long Description on the Product Detail Page\n Show Related Products on the Product Detail Page\n Show Product Specs on the Product Detail Page\n Make Documentation Available on the Product Detail Page\n Show Custom Document Types on the Product Detail Page\n Show Shipping Information on the Product Detail Page\n Show Custom Content on the Product Detail Page\n Product List Page\n Scaled Cart Page\n Shopping Cart Page\n Site Login Page\n Site Register Page\n Modify the Column Layout of a Storefront Page\n Add Widgets to Storefront Pages with Visualforce Components\n Customize Storefront Headings and Text with Page Labels\n Provide Intuitive Storefront Navigation with Menus\n Author Custom Content for a Storefront Page\n Style Your Storefront with a Theme\n Extend the Default Storefront Pages\n Source Options for Storefront Media\n Allow Only One Country, Territory, or State in Address Picklists\n Strategize for Storefront Success\n Deliver Storefront Performance and Security\n Market Templates for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n Solution Resources for B2B Commerce for Visualforce\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nVISUALFORCE B2B COMMERCE\nShow a Product's Long Description on the Product Detail Page\n\nA product's short description is limited to 2,000 characters. What if you have a more detailed description that you want to show on the Product Detail page? You can create a page section that shows a product's long description, which supports up to 5,000 characters.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\n\nSalesforce Compatibility\n\nSalesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience for Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.\n\n\n\n\nB2B Commerce Compatibility\n\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Winter ’21 (version 4.13)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’20 (version 4.12)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’19 (version 4.11)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Spring ’19 (version 4.10)\nB2B Commerce for Visualforce Summer ’18 (version 4.9)\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo create CC Page Section records:\tCreate on CC Page Sections\n\nBoth the short description (1) and long description (2) become available on the Product Detail page. Optionally, you can separately hide the short description.\n\nEnter a long description in your CC Product records.\nCreate a page section configured to show the long description.\nOn the CC Page Sections tab in your org, click New.\nFor Display Type, select Tab or Widget.\nIf you selected Tab for Display Type, enter the name of your storefront's tab group in Grouping.\nNOTE The Product Detail page supports only one group of page section tabs. In the Capricorn Coffee demo storefront, the default tab group name is tabSec.\nFor Page Name, select ProductDetails.\nFor Section Name, select Content.\nFor Section Filter, select Description.\nFor Location, select Main Content or Right Column, depending on which Display Type you selected.\nEnter a Sequence value, specify a Storefront, and save your changes.\nNOTE To determine the order of tabs or widgets, B2B Commerce for Visualforce compares the Sequence values of all page sections with the same Display Type and Location. Lower Sequence values display first.\nRefresh your storefront.\nSEE ALSO\nCreate a Product for Your Storefront\nGuidelines for Creating Page Sections\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
